1. Start Eclipse and create a new workspace.
2. Setting up Tomcat configuration.
	a. Click on Windows -> Preferences
	b. On the right panel select Tomcat
	c. Select Tomcat version 5.x
	d. Specify the home directory of tomcat.
	e. Press OK.
	f. On the right panel expand Tomcat menu and select Advanced.
	g. Set up the Tomcat base directory.
	h. Press OK.
3. Select File -> New -> Project.
4. Expand Java and select Tomcat Project.
5. Insert the Project name, press next and the Finish.
6. Eclips will ask if you want to switch to the web perspective. Choose Yes.
7. Select the new project and right click. Select Import.
8. Select Zip file and press Next.
9. Choose the war file on the filesystem and select then "Overwrite existing
   resources without warning"
